## Supplemental Security Income (SSI) 

Supplemental Security Income pays monthly benefits to people with limited income who have a qualifying disability. Caregivers of children who are blind, deaf, drug affected, diagnosed with medical fragility, disability, or receive special education services are eligible for Supplemental Security Income (SSI) benefits. 

{% Callout %}
While the child is a dependent of the state of Washington, the Department will receive SSI on behalf of the child.
{% endCallout %}

