## Foster care reimbursements

Kinship caregivers can apply to become licensed by the Department, a private Child Placing Agency, or a tribe. Once licensed, caregivers receive [foster care reimbursements](https://www.dcyf.wa.gov/sites/default/files/pubs/LIC_0045.pdf) to help cover the cost of food, clothing, shelter, and personal incidentals.

{% Callout %}
DCYF still encourages caregivers to apply to TANF or non-needy relative TANF in order to receive financial assistance during the licensing process.
{% endCallout %}

