## Mileage or transportation costs 

DCYF will reimburse mileage or transportation costs for some activities including 

1. Family Time with parents ‚Äì the costs of transporting children to visits with their parents
2. Family Time with siblings ‚Äì the costs of transporting children to visits with their siblings 
3. Transportation to and from the parent-child/sibling Family Time visit that is longer than three hours and the caregiver returns home 
4. Transportation to maintain educational stability 
5. Court hearings 
6. Court-ordered activities 
7. Medical, dental, counseling sessions, or WIC appointments 
8. Attendance at child/youth specific meetings at the request of DCYF staff 
9. Child specific DCYF approved caregiver trainings include (for which no subsidy is offered through the Alliance for Child Welfare): 
	- Trainings specific to the needs of children in the home
	- First Aid and HIV/BBP training 
10. Participation in school-related extracurricular activities 
11. Participation in recreational activities, practices, or lessons 
12. Transportation to and from respite, for mileage in excess of 10 miles each way 
13. Transportation to and from child care, for mileage in excess of the caregiver‚Äôs regular commute to work
14. Transportation to and from a child‚Äôs appointment that is longer than three hours and the caregiver returns home 
15. Other transportation necessary to meet the needs of the child identified in ongoing case planning

Some transportation costs are not covered, such as transit for: 

1. Haircuts 
2. Birthday parties or shopping 
3. Sports events 
4. School ‚Äì except as indicated in #4 (above) 

Use the [Caregiver Monthly Transportation Reimbursement form](https://www.dcyf.wa.gov/forms?field_number_value=07-090&title=) and submit this to your social worker. 

## [Property damage and emergency medical treatment](https://www.dcyf.wa.gov/sites/default/files/pubs/FB_0011.pdf) reimbursement 

The Foster Caregiver Reimbursement Program Provides limited reimbursement for damages to property owned by the foster caregiver and/or emergency medical treatment for household members because of an act by a child experiencing foster care who is placed in the home.

Use the [foster caregiver reimbursement claim form](https://www.dcyf.wa.gov/forms?field_number_value=18-400&title=) to submit a claim. 

The Third Party Liability Program Provides limited reimbursement for damages to property owned by a third party and/or a third party emergency medical treatment that the foster caregiver is responsible for because of an act of either the foster caregiver or a child experiencing foster care who is placed in the home

Use the [foster caregiver third party liability form](https://www.dcyf.wa.gov/forms?field_number_value=18-400A&title=) to submit a claim. 